revision.text:
{{DISPLAYTITLE:Floor_RaiseByValueTimes8}} {{Special|35|tag, speed, height|Floor|RaiseByValueTimes8}}
* ''tag'': Tag of affected sector * ''speed'': How quickly the floor moves * ''height'': Amount to raise floor by
Raises a tagged sector's floor by (''height'' * 8) units. If ''tag'' is 0, then the sector on the line's back side is used. This special is useful in the Hexen [[map format]] where argument cannot exceed 255; in [[UDMF]] large values can be used with [[Floor_RaiseByValue]].
== Examples ==
{{noexamples}}
== Conversions from linedef types == The following Doom map format types can be converted as Floor_RaiseByValueTimes8: {| {{prettytable}} !Type!!Conversion!!Trigger |- |{{icon|Doom}} 140:S1 Floor Up 512 || Floor_RaiseByValueTimes8(tag, {{xlat|F_SLOW}}, 64) || Player Use |- |{{icon|Strife}} 140:S1 Floor Up 512 || Floor_RaiseByValueTimes8(tag, {{xlat|F_SLOW}}, 64) || Player Use |- |{{icon|Boom}} 142:W1 Floor Up 512 || Floor_RaiseByValueTimes8(tag, {{xlat|F_SLOW}}, 64) || Player Cross |- |{{icon|Boom}} 147:WR Floor Up 512 || Floor_RaiseByValueTimes8(tag, {{xlat|F_SLOW}}, 64) || Player Cross, Repeatable |- |{{icon|Boom}} 178:SR Floor Up 512 || Floor_RaiseByValueTimes8(tag, {{xlat|F_SLOW}}, 64) || Player Use, Repeatable |}
